/*
:name: const_bit_select
:type: equiv_slang
:verilog_top: const_bit_select.top
:pyrope_top: const_bit_select.top
*/

// Minimal repro of the verification.html "lhd lec ERROR" category
// InvalidSelectExpression (small_todo_working.md "Still open" #3): cgen emits a
// bit-select applied directly to a CONSTANT literal, e.g.
//   get_mask_20_u = (9'sb1????????)[15:12];
// which slang's semantic checker rejects ("select expression is not allowed
// here" / "cannot select range of [15:12] from 'logic signed[8:0]'"), so the
// LEC that reads the regenerated Verilog ERRORS instead of proving.
//
// The trigger: a signed const with a known sign bit and UNKNOWN low bits
// (`cur = 0sb1????????`) bit-selected ABOVE its width (`#[12..=15]`, entirely in
// the sign-extension region) INSIDE a mux arm — cprop keeps the Get_mask
// structural (a const `a` operand with unknowns) instead of folding it, and cgen
// emits `(const)[hi:lo]`. The select is fully determined (all sign bits ⇒ 0xf),
// so the fix is to compute the sliced constant at cgen time. This mirrors the
// XiangShan ExceptionGen/CVT32/DataPath families (a `#[97..=115]` slice of a
// 65-bit signed const-with-unknowns in a dead mux arm).
//
// FIXED (2026-07-01) in inou/cgen/cgen_verilog.cpp: the Get_mask handler now
// folds a const `a` operand via `Dlop::get_mask_op(mask)` and emits the resulting
// literal (`5'shf`) instead of `(const)[range]`. Guards prp-equiv-const_bit_select.
pub comb top(sel:u1, b:s9) -> (o:u4) {
  mut cur:s9 = 0sb1????????
  if sel {
    o = cur#[12..=15]
  } else {
    o = b#[12..=15]
  }
}
